337
00:20:10,766 --> 00:20:14,208
from Games Hub captured it in a really great way, which we were really thrilled

338
00:20:14,228 --> 00:20:15,309
to see when she said.

339
00:20:16,175 --> 00:20:19,439
This. There were some small moments where I was unsure of what to do.

340
00:20:19,459 --> 00:20:23,123
And while this did leave me wandering the halls aimlessly for a brief time,

341
00:20:23,243 --> 00:20:27,088
it ultimately felt like this added to the overall feeling that you really are Casey,

342
00:20:27,508 --> 00:20:31,913
wanting to help, but unsure how. And that's the exact feeling that we were trying to create, is like

343
00:20:32,294 --> 00:20:37,818
We don't necessarily need for this to be this action-packed, rising action kind of experience.

344
00:20:37,838 --> 00:20:42,082
We wanted the player to have moments of really deep, heartfelt connection, but then also moments

345
00:20:42,182 --> 00:20:48,147
of boredom, or moments of not knowing what to do, or moments of trying to figure out how to be helpful.

346
00:20:49,227 --> 00:20:51,608
I also want to talk about the narrative shape of the game.

